      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 248,
      "message": "This message is too generic because it can be about just any request. Put yourself in the troubleshooting shoes - this message in a log probably won't help much. Write what exactly was being done when an error happened. Also, add some info about how it is acted upon. For example: \"Ignored as the request is not mission critical\". Probably add suggestions for fixing it (e.g. \"Check configuration and make sure the catalog server is accessible\"). That will also serve as in-code documentation.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 329,
        "name": "Vitaly Emporopulo",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "Vitaliy.Emporopulo@amdocs.com",
        "username": "vempo"
